<subSubSection lastPageId="56" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 72" captionStartId="F72" captionText="Figure 72. Distribution of Conostegia brenesii." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure72" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96430" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">72</figureCitation>
). Endemic to cloud forests on the Caribbean slope of the Central and Tilaran cordilleras in Costa Rica, 1100-1750 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="974181" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure72" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96430" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" start="Figure 72" startId="F72">
<paragraph pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Figure 72.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia brenesii" order="Myrtales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brenesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Conostegia brenesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph lastPageId="56" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia brenesii" order="Myrtales" pageId="55" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brenesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Conostegia brenesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very distinctive and narrow endemic of middle elevation cloud forests in Costa Rica. It can be easily distinguished by its dense indument of stipitate stellate hairs on all plant parts. Because of its dense indument of stipitate stel 
<pageBreakToken pageId="56" pageNumber="57" start="start">late</pageBreakToken>
hairs it is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia caelestis" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caelestis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia caelestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which is allopatric occurring in northern Central America. In addition, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia brenesii" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brenesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia brenesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tends to be a shrubby species whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia caelestis" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caelestis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia caelestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
tends to be a larger tree. The flowering time differs with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia caelestis" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caelestis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia caelestis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowering in the first half of the year and 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia brenesii" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brenesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia brenesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
flowering in the second half of the year consistently from July to September. The molecular phylogeny does not place these species as sister taxa, which suggests convergent evolution in the dense stipitate stellate indument (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Infrageneric classification in Conostegia next to the recently generated molecular phylogenetic hypothesis of Conostegia. Colors show the classification proposed by Schnell (1996). To the right of the phylogeny is the sectional classification proposed here. The phylogeny is a slightly modified version of the majority rule consensus tree derived from a Bayesian analysis of DNA sequences from four chloroplast regions and two nuclear ribosomal spacers (Kriebel et al. 2015) pruned to one accession per species." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96359" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">1</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia brenesii" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brenesii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia brenesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
falls sister to the 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia montana" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
- 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia setosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Conostegia setosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex in the molecular phylogeny.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
